The only experiment Ι was enabled to make, was collecting a small quan- tity of rye grains from ears which were strongly infected with ergots, and sowing these separately, but they did not produce one infected ear.

The cause of this disease being yet totally unknown, it would be presump- tuous and idle to talk of remedies to prevent or cure it; that must be left till the real cause is discovered.
